# Frontend Rules — Next.js App Router

## Component conventions
- Server components by default — only add "use client" when component needs hooks or events
- File naming: kebab-case (run-scenario-form.tsx, run-history.tsx)
- One component per file — no barrel exports needed for small projects
- shadcn/ui components only — never raw HTML form/button/input elements

## Data fetching
- All server state via TanStack Query (useQuery, useMutation) — never useEffect + fetch
- Mutations must invalidate the relevant query on success
- Always handle loading and error states — never leave them undefined
- API client in lib/api.ts — never inline fetch() calls in components

## Forms
- React Hook Form for ALL forms — never controlled inputs with useState
- Always use zod resolver for schema validation
- Submit button disabled while mutation is pending

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS only — no inline styles, no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Use shadcn/ui component variants for color/state — never custom color classes on shadcn components
- Responsive by default — consider mobile layout even if desktop-first

## Environment
- API base URL from NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL — never hardcode localhost:4000
